{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c049cecf-9fa5-488b-b9a9-10604d32d6f6","content":"To migrate your NUnit test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Update your packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it includes the MTP adapter).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n\n2. **Enable the platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key changes to be aware of:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter v5+ targets MTP natively; the VSTest bridge is opt-in (reversed from before).\n- If you use `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>` or a custom `Program.cs`, see [NUnit MTP docs](https://docs.nunit.org/articles/vs-test-adapter/Microsoft-Testing-Platform.html) for entry-point guidance.\n- `.runsettings` files still work, but some VSTest-specific settings may need adjustment.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2715117f-d222-4b4f-ab2b-d10620c3e1d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question, not a code change request. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":346},"id":"9a9305d9-dd2a-4893-9e69-1a958bbb7b64","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:51.655Z","parentId":"ecb22e71-3191-468d-962b-bbe82aa830a8"}
